ent-MedievalClothingNeckRoyalCloak = snow-white mantle
    .desc = A mantle of wealthy Merchants from a rich family, the merchants spent a lot of money, definitely the Whitelights.
ent-MedievalClothingNeckRoyalCloakAlt = snow-white mantle
ent-MedievalClothingHandsRoyalGloves = snow-white gloves
    .desc = Silky and pleasant to the touch gloves, definitely custom-made.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterRoyalCoat = noble overcoat
    .desc = A sturdy overcoat made by the best craftsmen of the trade islands, the colors and gilding refer to the Whitelights, who have merchant connections in Legion ports.
ent-ClothingBeltRoyalSheath = noble scabbard
    .desc = Gilded scabbard made from the finest leather.
ent-MedievalClothingRoyalBoots = embellished boots
    .desc = Sturdy footwear combining style and comfort, the sole is quite soft and durable.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterRoyalArmorUpIron = Whitelight heavy plate armor
    .desc = Armor composed of metal plates forged to the customer's physique, covering everything entirely. The cuirass is adorned and gilded. A fabric skirt hangs from the belt.
ent-MedievalClothingRoyalFeetSteel = Whitelight sabatons
    .desc = Brightly decorated plate footwear, fastened to the lower part of the greaves. Painted in the colors of the dynasty of the noble Merchants.
ent-MedievalRoyalIronGloves = snow-white plate gauntlets
    .desc = Knightly gauntlets with segmented construction for protecting the hands and forearms, patterns are applied on the surface. The Whitelight heraldry is on the back of the gauntlets.
ent-MedievalClothingRoyalMask = half mask
    .desc = A Venetian-style mask depicting half a face, colored in golden hues with a white body. Does not hide the wearer's identity but adorns the face. On the back of the mask is written in ink "Whitelight".
ent-MedievalClothingHeadRoyalHelmet = noble helmet
    .desc = A custom-made Armet with a visor, adorned with a plume, a red feather. The gorget flows into the base of the neck, where a rondel is fastened. The sharp visor is decorated with gilding.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadRoyalHoop = noble hoop
    .desc = A golden hoop beautifully decorated with patterns, carrying the history of the Whitelight dynasty in their prosperity. There is a stone in the middle, resembling a ruby.
ent-MedievalIronRoyalSword = longsword of the Whitelight Saints
    .desc = A longsword adorned with gemstones with gilded metal. This is a truly a land of lustrous.
ent-MedievalSteelRoyalSword = longsword of the Whitelight Saints
ent-AhrimanStaffMedieval = black staff
    .desc = "Calmly moving the staff aside, the champion folded his arms." Once a great weapon, now it has lost its power.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCollegiumHatBaronSaturday = black top hat
    .desc = A top hat, surrounded by a necklace of skulls, and a cinnabar-coloured feather. Don't bring this hat anywhere close to phosphophyllite.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerLightBaronSaturday = black frock coat
    .desc = An expensive and stately suit made in Victorian style.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerLightPurpleScar = alienated star hood
    .desc = A dense hood made of fabric with a starry coating. In the center, a bright nebula fire eclipses the face of the wearer and possibly even their mind. Someone really did not want to see the cruelty of this world.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerWeakPurpleScar = alienated star hood
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerLightPurpleScar = dichotomy garment
    .desc = Robes made of dense material, so dense that it seems to become one with its wearer. It tries to embrace and protect you, or perhaps strangle and harm you?
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerWeakPurpleScar = dichotomy garment
ent-MedievalShoesCharmerPurpleScar = stellar iscariot treads
    .desc = Footwear made of hard, polished material. Prolonged wearing will deprive you of the feeling in your feet, and still, despite this, you will continue to walk, but... I felt like that’s what wanted “Kivonne painting by Cezanne”.
ent-MedievalClothingHandsGlovesPurpleScar = alienation gloves
    .desc = Gloves made of iridescent stellar alloy. They have memorized the movement of the hands, but... I felt like that’s what wanted “Kivonne painting by Cezanne”.
ent-MedievalClothingUniformJumpsuitShitCloth77 = runic jumpsuit
    .desc = A purple garment. The fabric is decorated with small runic signs that form a composition of a full canvas and are completely invisible from a distance. Some can see among the runes a healing spell, but it is crossed out and replaced with something unfamiliar...
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerNecro2 = cursed magic robe
    .desc = Every thread of this mantle is imbued with mana.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerNecro = cursed protective robe
    .desc = Despite being cursed it still manages to protect its owner.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorUpIronDarkArmorArchaont = dark chestplate
    .desc = An indistinctly black armor made of durable material. On some of its parts, symbols dedicated to ancient gods can be seen. On the back of the armor, an incredibly strong leather cloak, scorched by hellish flame, is visible. The cloak has no free space, it's entirely covered in symbols. On the shoulders are two human skulls that seem to be bleeding.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCrusaderDarkHelmetArchaont = dark helmet
    .desc = An unnaturally black helmet on which patterns and symbols of ancient gods are visible. On the sides of the helmet are two majestic tusks of an unknown animal. The eyes unnaturally shine with scarlet flame, while on the forehead another fiery point is displayed; it's not possible to determine exactly what it is, an eye or something else.
ent-MedievalClothingFeetSteelDarkBootsArchaont = dark boots
    .desc = Sabatons of an unnaturally black color, made of an unknown material on which patterns and symbols of ancient gods are visible.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCrusaderMorbius = ceremonial helmet
    .desc = This is not just a helmet, but a gateway. Anyone who wears it for too long begins to hear the call of Morbius. First in dreams, then while awake, but in the end, the owner forgets their name... but the helmet remembers.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorUpIronMorbius = ceremonial shell
    .desc = Feels neither metal nor fabric, more like chitin, grown in some otherworldly realm. Patterns are inscribed upon it, symbols of the deity Morbius. They seem to be pulsating.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorWhiteWizardCharmerLight = snow-white robe
    .desc = An enchanted robe, adorned with equally snow-white gemstones. Don't bring this anywhere close to phosphophyllite.
ent-MedievalClothingHandsGlovesWhiteWizard = snow-white globes
    .desc = Velvet gloves that are pleasant to touch.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerLightWhiteWizard = snow-white hood
    .desc = The hood of the enchanted robe.
ent-MedievalClothingNeckCloakRoyalLegionEagle = azure cloak
    .desc = A long cloak richly made in the colors of the local state, accomplished with golden threads. It fastens around the neck with golden armatures and clasps, crafted by master tailors and blacksmiths in a combined effort. The Legion's coat of arms adorns the back. Necessary for friend-or-foe identification.
ent-MedievalClothingNeckCloakRoyalInsFox = bloodied cloak
    .desc = A bloody red cloak reaching the wearer's feet, enveloping the torso and covering the neck with edges, bound with silver threads, clasps and armatures. The work was done by local artisans who embraced the Rebellion's cause. There is beautiful fur around the neck for protection from frost. Necessary for friend-or-foe identification.
ent-MedievalClothingBlackBoots = dark boots
    .desc = Sturdy leather traveling boots.
ent-MedievalClothingHandsBlackGloves = dark gloves
    .desc = Comfortable and lightweight gloves.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterBlackArmorLeather = dark suit
    .desc = A comfortable suit with sturdy leather inserts, barely hindering your movement.
ent-MedievalClothingHelmetBlackLeather = dark hood
    .desc = A lightweight hood with a mask, concealing your identity.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerLightAncientMage = ancient mantle
    .desc = An unusual mantle, shrouded in enchanted plates of unknown origin with glowing runes.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerLightAncientMage = hood
    .desc = Once could have driven its wearer and surrounding people mad, but now it has lost its power, yet you still hear a certain whisper...
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerWeakStrayMage = wandering mage mage
    .desc = A tattered mantle with faded cloth colors. The fabrics protect the wearer from heat and contains warmth. A magical essence emits from every thread woven together, occasionally releasing a faint glow.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerWeakStrayMage = gathered cloak
    .desc = A dense piece of cloth covering the wearer's shoulders and half of their head. Possesses magical properties that enhance the wearer's vitality. In some places, there are worn patches, dirt.
