ent-MedievalRoyalWoodenShield = teardrop heraldy
    .desc = A large shield made from wooden planks layered upon each other. In the center, one can notice the heraldry of house "Whitelight" and a silver boss, pointed towards the corners. Strong, large, and quite light.
ent-MedievalRoyalWoodenShieldKnight = knight shield with heraldy
    .desc = A flat shield shaped from bent wood with a dangling strap on the reverse. The front is adorned with the heraldry of house "Whitelight", a round boss is fixed in the center. It tapers towards the bottom to protect one of the limbs.
ent-MedievalClothingOuteRoyalArmorIronCuirassLight = Whitelight lightened cuirass
    .desc = An iron cuirass draped with cloth embroidered with the coat of arms of a noble family. You can recognize this coat of arms, it's definitely "Whitelight". Good protection for its wearer. Made of felt, covered with iron sheets in a hinged connection.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterRoyalArmorIronCuirass = Whitelight sturdy cuirass
    .desc = A heavier variant of the cuirass with additional plates hung on the felt, many straps dangling from the shoulders and back. The armor bears the heraldry of the "Whitelight" dynasty. Probably the owner opted for a sturdier protection.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterHorseRoyalArmorUpIron = Whitelight plate horse armor
    .desc = Armor made of snow-white plates, adorned with gold inlays, flags with the Belosvet coat of arms adorn the sides.
    .suffix = { "SKIN, Medieval, clothing, transport" }
