medieval-skeletron-description = The servants of Morbius have arrived to restore the cursed skull! Intercept them before it's too late!
medieval-skeletron-title = Morbius
ent-MedievalClothingUniformJumpsuitShitCloth74 = worn dress
    .desc = A worn dress made from animal hides.
ent-MedievalClothingUniformJumpsuitShitCloth75 = snow-white gambeson
    .desc = A white padded under-armor garment made from several layers of dense fabric, featuring red ribbons and threads on top. Quilted material stuffed with cloth and leather. Narrow and tight, it fits the warrior of the "Whitelight" dynasty. A vertical pattern of parallel seams, with tow, cloth, and yarn pieces stuffed between them.
ent-MedievalClothingNeckCloakSpookyVendigo = grim cloak
    .desc = A grim cloak made from a wendigo hide.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetLegionOpcionWeakRoyal = Whitelight optio weisenau
    .desc = A Weisenau-type helmet modified with additional plates and painted in the dynastic colors of the "Whitelight" family. The helmet is depicted in a dome-shaped style with a wide neck guard and hanging red straps. On the forehead, a golden plate with a silver nasal piece, made from two metal alloys, shone. Officer's authority. A red-and-white vertical crest on the stem.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetRoyalLegioner = Whitelight infantryman weisenau
    .desc = A Weisenau-type helmet modified with additional plates and painted in the dynastic colors of the "Whitelight" family. The helmet is depicted in a dome-shaped style with a wide neck guard and hanging red straps. On the forehead, a golden plate shone, which, although made of soft metal, could add to the protection class.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerPurple = college archmage robe
    .desc = A dark purple robe with a simple yet stylish cut. Nothing extra - just comfort and a very slight hint of mystery.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerPurple = college archmage hood
    .desc = A deep hood shaded in dark purple. Hides the face well but doesn't obstruct the view, or does it?
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerLightPurple = college mage robe
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerLightPurple = college mage hood
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerWeakApocrif = Mor novice robe
    .desc = An almost unremarkable robe, except for unknown symbols and a faint mysterious aura, but I guess that's fine.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerLightApocrif = Mor mage robe
    .desc = A light robe equipped with mana-conducting alloy. It emits mystery and knowledge.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerLightApocrif = Mor mage mask
    .desc = A mask shaped like an octopus, made of an unknown material. It exudes humility and submission. It is not known how the wearer sees through it, likely the result of mysterious magic. It emits an octopus aura (whatever that is supposed to mean).
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorCharmerApocrif = Hermaeus-Mor robe
    .desc = An incredibly beautiful mantle. Embroidered from a material unknown to humanity, with metal trimmings that emphasize status and increase the robe's mana conductivity. It is imbued with the scent of forbidden knowledge. On the chest, there is an amulet shaped like an octopus visible. Seems like it was made from the same material as the trimmings.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetCharmerApocrif = Hermaues-Mor mask
    .desc = A mask made of an unknown mana-conducting material, shaped like a face with tentacles, I wonder what's it's use? It fills the air with the smell of rotten books.
ent-MedievalClothingApocrifBoots = Hermaeus-Mor boots
    .desc = Made entirely of metal of unknown origin, despite their bulkiness, they preserve mobility and are designed for mana accumulation.
ent-MedievalClothingApocrifBootsLight = Mor mage boots
    .desc = Elegant mana-conducting boots with the smell of rotten books.
ent-MedievalClothingApocrifBootsWeak = Mora novice boots
    .desc = Almost unremarkable boots, except for unknown symbols and a mysterious aura.
ent-MedievalClothingHandsApocrif = Hermaues-Mor gloves
    .desc = Made entirely of metal of unknown origin, with small spikes  all over the glove.
ent-MedievalClothingNeckCloakViking = fur cloak
    .desc = A cloak woven from animal hides, featuring warm fur.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorChainMailViking = northman chailmail
    .desc = Chainmail with worn rings and repaired sections. It's clear it's been worn for a long time and not in the calmest places. But it knows its job.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetViking = northman helmet
    .desc = A sturdy steel helmet with a gilded border and a short crest.
ent-MedievalFalshionT3LegionViking = enchanted dagger
    .desc = A blade forged on distant islands from unknown steel, this steel has a unique property - emitted light.
ent-MedievalFalshionT3SteelViking = enchanted dagger
ent-MedievalClothingUniformJumpsuitShitCloth76 = snow-white cassock
    .desc = The lower vestment of clergy and monks, a long ankle-length garment with long narrow sleeves. A white cassock of straight cut, that fastens edge-to-edge and is wrapped with a golden cloth belt. The robe is soft, pleasant to the touch, and made of linen. You can notice the shades of the famous merchant dynasty "Whitelight," and the family member or a close house member has become a monk.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterRoyalChaplain = radiant robe
    .desc = The vestments of a divine child, who dedicates their life under the authority of one of the gods of the Legion lands. The colors themselves refer to the belonging of the ascetic monk to the "Whitelight" lineage, who was exiled by the senior family member into service. The robe is long, the sleeves fall past the wearer's wrists, and the garments themselves are loose and wide - hanging down to the legs.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHatRoyalChaplain = holy visage
    .desc = A solid-drawn conical helmet made of gold, wrapped with additional elements of plates and long needles. Looking closely, you can see the outlines of the Matriarch's visage depicted on the facial part of the helmet-mask. The helmet's rim is formed from steel sheets, painted in black gold, and fastens the mask parts. Removing and flipping the helmet, you can notice the signature "Whitelight."
ent-MedievalClothingRoyalChaplainBoots = luxurious sandals
    .desc = Richly decorated and well-made travel and pilgrimage shoes for a monk. The sole has a heel shape, there are a couple of straps made of soft leather that fasten to the cassock. The leather itself is light and was made by the best shoemakers on the continent.
ent-MedievalFireFetter = fire shackles
    .desc = Magical shackles created from fire magic. Upon hitting, they deal fire damage and set the target on fire.
ent-MedievalCursedFetter = shadow shackles
    .desc = Magical shackles created from cursed magic. Upon hitting, they deal stamina damage.
ent-MedievalActionFireFetter = Fire shackles
    .desc = Summons magical fire shackles into the hand. Upon hitting, they deal fire damage and set the target on fire. Costs 35 essence of fire.
    .suffix = { "Medieval, magic" }
ent-MedievalActionCursedFetter = Shadow shackles
    .desc = Summons magical cursed shackles into the hand. Upon hitting, they deal stamina damage. Costs 35 essence of darkness.
