ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetLegionOpcionRoyal = Whitelight Tribune weisenau
    .desc = A Weisenau-type helmet modified with additional plates and painted in the dynastic colors of the Whitelight family. The helmet is depicted in a domed style with a wide neck guard and hanging red straps. The forehead featured a gold plate with a silver nasal guard made from two metal alloys. Prestige over the infantry. The crest on the post was red.
ent-MedievalClothingHeadHelmetLegionLegatRoyal = Whitelight Legate weisenau
    .desc = A Weisenau-type helmet modified with additional plates and painted in the dynastic colors of the Whitelight family. The helmet is depicted in a domed style with a wide neck guard and hanging red straps. The forehead featured a full gold plate made from a harder metal alloy than that of a regular infantryman. The crest on the post was a red hue with white centered coloring.
ent-MedievalWoodenShieldBucklerRoyal = round shield
    .desc = A round shield on which the heraldry of the Whitelight dynasty was painted in bright colors. The wooden parts were made from the best wood, skillfully and expertly crafted. The hand of a master carpenter is evident in the work on the shield.
ent-RoyalBible = scriputre of the Mother
    .desc = A large book with the heraldry of the Whitelight dynasty on the cover, painted in white colors with a red cloth bookmark. The pages contain handwritten texts of faith in the Fierce Mother. In the corner, an unknown substance has already been absorbed.
ent-MedievalClothingBackpackSatchelLeatherRoyal = luxuriously decorated satchel
    .desc = A convenient and capacious bag of a representative of the wealthy classes. Opening it, you could see the main compartment and several small ones for separating different supplies, items, and trinkets. The color palette reminds you of the famous Whitelight merchants; apparently, they have opened a new formation of an atelier for making their own spacious bags, backpacks, and sacks.
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorLeatherRoyal = light vest
ent-MedievalClothingOuterArmorFurRoyal = spaulder with belt
    .desc = A leather spaulder with dark overlays formed over the main part of the leather. Golden armatures hold a strap that wraps around the body and holds the weak armor on the shoulder. It is unlikely that this type of armor will protect its owner. You can recognize the reverse colors of the Whitelight dynasty, apparently, they spared white dye for such an unnecessary wardrobe element.
